#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:2
msgid "fish_delta - compare functions and completions to the default"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:7
msgid ""
"fish_delta name ...\n"
"fish_delta [-f | --no-functions] [-c | --no-completions] [-C | --no-config] "
"[-d | --no-diff] [-n | --new] [-V | --vendor=]\n"
"fish_delta [-h | --help]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:17
msgid ""
"The ``fish_delta`` function tells you, at a glance, which of your functions "
"and completions differ from the set that fish ships."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:19
msgid ""
"It does this by going through the relevant variables (:envvar:"
"`fish_function_path` for functions and :envvar:`fish_complete_path` for "
"completions) and comparing the files against fish's default directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:21
msgid ""
"If any names are given, it will only compare files by those names (plus a \"."
"fish\" extension)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:23
msgid ""
"By default, it will also use ``diff`` to display the difference between the "
"files. If ``diff`` is unavailable, it will skip it, but in that case it also "
"cannot figure out if the files really differ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:25
msgid ""
"The exit status is 1 if there was a difference and 2 for other errors, "
"otherwise 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:28
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:30
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:32
msgid "**-f** or **--no-functions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:33
msgid "Stops checking functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:35
msgid "**-c** or **--no-completions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:36
msgid "Stops checking completions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:38
msgid "**-C** or **--no-config**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:39
msgid ""
"Stops checking configuration files like config.fish or snippets in the conf."
"d directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:41
msgid "**-d** or **--no-diff**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:42
msgid ""
"Removes the diff display (this happens automatically if ``diff`` can't be "
"found)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:44
msgid "**-n** or **--new**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:45
msgid ""
"Also prints new files (i.e. those that can't be found in fish's default "
"directories)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:47
msgid "**-Vvalue** or **--vendor=value**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:48
msgid "Determines how the vendor directories are counted. Valid values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:50
msgid ""
"\"default\" - counts vendor files as belonging to the defaults. Any changes "
"in other directories will be counted as changes over them. This is the "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:51
msgid ""
"\"user\" - counts vendor files as belonging to the user files. Any changes "
"in them will be counted as new or changed files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:52
msgid ""
"\"ignore\" - ignores vendor directories. Files of the same name will be "
"counted as \"new\" if no file of the same name in fish's default directories "
"exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:54
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:55
msgid "Prints ``fish_delta``'s help (this)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:58
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:60
msgid "Running just::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:62
msgid "fish_delta"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:64
msgid ""
"will give you a list of all your changed functions and completions, "
"including diffs (if you have the ``diff`` command)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:66
msgid "It might look like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:68
msgid ""
"> fish_delta\n"
"New: /home/alfa/.config/fish/functions/battery.fish\n"
"Changed: /home/alfa/.config/fish/test/completions/cargo.fish\n"
"--- /home/alfa/.config/fish/test/completions/cargo.fish 2022-09-02 "
"12:57:55.579229959 +0200\n"
"+++ /usr/share/fish/completions/cargo.fish      2022-09-25 "
"17:51:53.000000000 +0200\n"
"# the output of `diff` follows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:75
msgid ""
"The options are there to select which parts of the output you want. With ``--"
"no-completions`` you can compare just functions, and with ``--no-diff`` you "
"can turn off the ``diff`` display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:77
msgid "To only compare your ``fish_git_prompt``, you might use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:79
msgid "fish_delta --no-completions fish_git_prompt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_delta.rst:81
msgid "which will only compare files called \"fish_git_prompt.fish\"."
msgstr ""
